    <p>Other parts of the world may be ex­pe­ri­enc­ing scorch­ing sum­mers but Sin­ga­pore­ans have been don­ning rainy-day gear. Rain­fall and a par­tic­u­larly wet June have brought cooler weather. This is ex­pected to per­sist through­out this month, with the mer­cury dipping to 22 deg C on some days and more rain­fall than in the past fort­night, the weath­er­man said last Thurs­day.</p>


